abstract: The service, known as MI5, argued that sources sometimes had to be allowed to break the law so that officers could prevent more serious offenses. Critics say the policy offers de facto impunity.
snippet: The service, known as MI5, argued that sources sometimes had to be allowed to break the law so that officers could prevent more serious offenses. Critics say the policy offers de facto impunity.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — A British court has upheld a government policy that allows informants of the British domestic intelligence service to commit crimes when it is deemed to be in the interest of national security, in a case that judges said exposed a tension between the rule of law and public safety.

abstract: Bosnia have named former Yugoslavia striker Dusan Bajevic as their new head coach in a bid to reach the Euro 2020 finals, the Balkan nation's Football Association (NFSBIH) said on Saturday.
snippet: Bosnia have named former Yugoslavia striker Dusan Bajevic as their new head coach in a bid to reach the Euro 2020 finals, the Balkan nation's Football Association (NFSBIH) said on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: SARAJEVO — Bosnia have named former Yugoslavia striker Dusan Bajevic as their new head coach in a bid to reach the Euro 2020 finals, the Balkan nation's Football Association (NFSBIH) said on Saturday.
headline_main: Former Striker Bajevic Takes Over as Bosnia Coach
headline_print_headline: Former Striker Bajevic Takes Over as Bosnia Coach

abstract: France is the only Western country with a significant military presence in a region of West Africa where several countries are fighting Islamist insurgencies.
snippet: France is the only Western country with a significant military presence in a region of West Africa where several countries are fighting Islamist insurgencies.
lead_paragraph: ABIDJAN, Ivory Coast — French forces killed 33 militants on Saturday in Mali near the border with Mauritania, President Emmanuel Macron of France said.

abstract: Like Americans, Britons are jettisoning longtime political allegiances in a sign of new cultural divides.
snippet: Like Americans, Britons are jettisoning longtime political allegiances in a sign of new cultural divides.
lead_paragraph: Britain has been rocked by eight major electoral contests in the last nine years. Four general elections, two referendums on Scotland’s independence and European Union membership and two sets of European Parliament elections have pushed one of the world’s oldest and historically most stable democracies into a period of churn and change.

abstract: At the end of 1919, the Bolsheviks were consolidating power in Russia, and spreading their message abroad.
snippet: At the end of 1919, the Bolsheviks were consolidating power in Russia, and spreading their message abroad.
lead_paragraph: On Dec. 21, 1919, this newspaper reported that Bolshevik forces in Russia had won a sweeping victory along the Estonian border, capturing 2,500 prisoners in a campaign to solidify their northwestern border. For a moment, their future seemed bright. The month before in Petrograd, about 100 miles to the northeast, the Bolsheviks had celebrated the second anniversary of the Soviet revolution with lengthy processions with red banners and brass bands. Grigory Zinoviev, chairman of the Petrograd Soviet, had stood on a podium in the cold fall air, with factory workers, soldiers and sailors from the Baltic fleet arrayed below him, to report on the regime’s accomplishments for the last two years and its prospects for the immediate future.

abstract: Caretaker manager Duncan Ferguson ended his short tenure as Everton boss on a high note and welcomed the arrival of his more heralded successor Carlo Ancelotti after the trophy-laden Italian was appointed on Saturday.
snippet: Caretaker manager Duncan Ferguson ended his short tenure as Everton boss on a high note and welcomed the arrival of his more heralded successor Carlo Ancelotti after the trophy-laden Italian was appointed on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: LIVERPOOL, England — Caretaker manager Duncan Ferguson ended his short tenure as Everton boss on a high note and welcomed the arrival of his more heralded successor Carlo Ancelotti after the trophy-laden Italian was appointed on Saturday.
headline_main: Ferguson Hails Everton's Ancelotti Capture After Arsenal Draw

abstract: Prosecutors are looking to file four additional charges against an Indiana couple accused of abandoning their adopted daughter.

lead_paragraph: LAFAYETTE, Ind. — Prosecutors are looking to file four additional charges against an Indiana couple accused of abandoning their adopted daughter.
